**Analysis of the Main Target Image**

1. **Overall Block Count and Layers**

   - There are **18 total blocks** in the scene.  
   -  They arrange into two “buildings” (left and right), each with a red‐block base layer, a mid‐layer of cubes/half‐cylinders/rectangular prisms, and a top layer of roofs or horizontal beams.  In addition, the left building has three tall blocks standing behind it.

2. **Detailed Spatial Breakdown**

   - **Left Building**  
     • **Bottom layer:** three red blocks in a row.  The left two are clearly red arches (each with a visible curved opening).  The third is a red cube of the same height filling out the right side of this base.  
     • **Mid‐layer (front):**  
       – A blue cube sits atop the leftmost red arch.  
       – Two yellow half‐cylinders span across the middle arch (side‐by‐side).  
       – An orange cube sits on the red cube at the right end, topped by a red triangular roof.  
     • **Mid‐layer (rear/center):** a horizontal green rectangular beam bridging behind the half‐cylinders and under the roof line.  
     • **Rear verticals:** one tall green rectangular prism and two tall yellow rectangular prisms stand up behind the arches and cubes (the “back row” of the structure).

   - **Right Building**  
     • **Bottom layer:** two red “U‐shaped” curved blocks side by side, forming a wavelike base, plus a red cube at the far right corner.  
     • **Mid‐layer:** a blue cube rests on the curved blocks in the center, with a green rectangular beam spanning horizontally on top of the blue cube.  
     • **Top:** an orange triangular roof caps the green beam.

---

## 2. Selection of Required Dictionary Blocks

Below is the exact set of block indices (and how many times each is used) that match color, shape, and orientation **as shown**—no rotations allowed other than what is pictured in the dictionary:

• **#1 (Red Arch)** – used 2× (the two left‐building arches)  
• **#2 (Red “U” Block, open‐top)** – used 1× (part of right‐building base)  
• **#3 (Red “U” Block, mirrored)** – used 1× (part of right‐building base)  
• **#4** – not used  
• **#5 (Blue Cube)** – used 2× (one on the left building, one on the right)  
• **#6 (Orange Cube)** – used 1× (the orange mid tower on the left)  
• **#7 (Red Cube)** – used 2× (one at the left‐building base, one at the right‐building base)  
• **#8 (Green Rect. Beam, horizontal)** – used 2× (one bridging the left building, one atop the right blue cube)  
• **#9 (Green Rect. Beam, vertical)** – used 1× (the tall green piece behind the left building)  
• **#10** – not used  
• **#11 (Yellow Tall Rect.)** – used 2× (the two tall yellow pillars at the rear of the left building)  
• **#12 (Yellow Half‐Cylinder)** – used 2× (the two yellow half‐arches on the left building)  
• **#13** – not used  
• **#14 (Orange Triangular Roof)** – used 1× (the roof on the right building)  
• **#15** – not used  
• **#16 (Red Triangular Roof)** – used 1× (the roof atop the left orange cube)
